It explains the meaning of each term:
i = imaginary unit (√−1)
ħ (h-bar) = reduced Planck’s constant
Ψ (Psi) = the wave function (describes the quantum state of a particle)
m = mass of the particle
∇² = Laplacian (describes how the wave function changes in space)
V = potential energy (the forces acting on the particle)
The left side describes how the quantum state evolves over time.
The post also notes real-world applications: semiconductors, lasers, quantum sensors, and molecular modeling.
